close_reason: Mixed repeatable aliases now preserve argv ordering through a shared Commander accumulator; full gates pass.
body: "## Problem\n`pm create ... --ac A --ac B --ac C --ac D` silently stores ONLY D. Same class as pm-cf1u (repeated --tag last-wins) and pm-6mit (repeated --step last-wins), both fixed via the argv-level coalesceRepeatedListFlags mechanism gated by the CliFlagContract `list: true` marker — but `--ac` was never marked, so it still last-wins. For agents this is silent data loss on a governance-required field: three of four criteria vanish with exit 0 and no warning.\n\n## Reproduction (live, 2026-07-07, v2026.7.7)\nCreating pm-a9mc with four --ac flags stored only the fourth criterion (visible in the create output and the item's history stream); the criteria had to be re-joined manually via pm update with a single ;-separated string.\n\n## Fix direction\nMark the acceptance-criteria contract flag as list-coalescing and join accumulated values with '; ' (the established storage convention for multi-criterion items, e.g. pm-cfed). Sweep other scalar flags where an agent would plausibly repeat the flag (e.g. --link/--file style inputs) and either mark them or leave them single-value deliberately.\n\n## Non-overlap\npm-cf1u and pm-6mit are closed and their fixes verified for their flag sets; this is the uncovered remainder of that class, reproduced on the current release."
